1
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:14,533
It's been 17 years
since I last saw her.

2
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:16,600
That's when we graduated
from medical school.

3
00:00:16,667 --> 00:00:18,900
Class of 2007.

4
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:20,767
My birth year.

5
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:21,767
Danilo?
Bukoy.

6
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:23,833
You saw Baby Kayla?

7
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:25,167
A woman was carrying her.

8
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:26,367
She came out of your house.

9
00:00:26,433 --> 00:00:28,367
It was the first time I saw her.

10
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:29,433
That's why I remember

11
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:30,500
she didn't look like
a neighborhood resident.

12
00:00:30,567 --> 00:00:33,167
All my life, you've been
telling me I'm sick.

13
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:34,933
Are you really a doctor?

14
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:37,767
Are you questioning
my being a doctor?

15
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:40,767
Why are you injecting me
with a veterinary drug, Mommy?

16
00:00:40,833 --> 00:00:43,633
Of course, I'm giving you
the one for humans!

17
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:45,400
What are you doing, Mommy?

18
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:47,633
Weren't you hit that night?

19
00:00:47,700 --> 00:00:51,300
What if the woman who took
Baby Kayla did it to you?

20
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,667
Find that woman.

21
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:54,233
Bring my grandchild here.

22
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:55,467
Bring her home.

23
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:35,433
Aside from your baby,

24
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:41,367
another one was reported missing
during the landslide.

25
00:01:41,467 --> 00:01:43,567
Ma'am, did someone report

26
00:01:43,633 --> 00:01:46,700
a car driving around
the area that night?

27
00:01:46,767 --> 00:01:51,833
You better wait for Mr. Ben
so you can talk to him.

28
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:55,533
He'll be here because
we have a schedule today.

29
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:58,100
He was the barangay captain
at that time.

30
00:01:58,167 --> 00:02:03,267
Maybe someone reported to him
but failed to record it.

31
00:02:04,167 --> 00:02:05,500
- So please wait for him.
- Okay.

32
00:02:05,567 --> 00:02:06,367
Thank you.

33
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:34,867
Why haven't you eaten yet?

34
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:37,800
I don't have the appetite.

35
00:02:45,133 --> 00:02:46,267
You know, Mookie?

36
00:02:48,667 --> 00:02:51,000
I'm trying my best
to be kind to you.

37
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:52,667
So, please.

38
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:55,567
Don't try my patience.

39
00:02:59,033 --> 00:02:59,933
Here are your medicines.

40
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:00,967
Take it.

41
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,233
I don't want to, Mommy.

42
00:03:09,700 --> 00:03:11,400
Why are you so stubborn?

43
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,300
Because...

44
00:03:14,867 --> 00:03:20,900
I'm not sure if the medicines
you give me are safe to take.

45
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:28,333
I saw you burning
the Canixidol vial.

46
00:03:29,533 --> 00:03:30,567
Why, Mommy?

47
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:33,900
Is it because what
I said is true?

48
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:38,867
That it's for animals?

49
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:42,067
Is that why you're
hiding it from me?

50
00:03:42,133 --> 00:03:44,800
All these medicines
are for your illness.

51
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:47,967
These are all safe
for humans, Mookie!

52
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:53,400
Then, if it's safe, Mommy,
why don't you try it yourself?

53
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:56,833
Then I'll follow.

54
00:04:05,967 --> 00:04:07,867
I'm doing everything...

55
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:12,533
to be a good mother.

56
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:22,200
But why do you make me
feel like I'm so evil?

57
00:04:24,467 --> 00:04:26,667
You don't respect me anymore.

58
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:30,767
It's not like that, Mommy.

59
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:34,267
I just want to know

60
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:38,533
if the medicines you give me
are safe.

61
00:04:44,633 --> 00:04:46,567
Do you think I'll hurt you?

62
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:49,867
Do you really think

63
00:04:49,933 --> 00:04:53,200
I'll give you a medicine
that can harm you?

64
00:04:54,867 --> 00:04:57,200
I only want proof, Mommy.

65
00:04:57,933 --> 00:05:03,367
But I can't take your medicines
because I'm not sick!

66
00:05:04,567 --> 00:05:06,967
Me, too, Mommy. I'm not sick.

67
00:05:07,033 --> 00:05:10,167
You are sick, Mookie!

68
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:12,500
You are sick, dear.

69
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:15,133
And if you don't take
these medicines,

70
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,567
you can get worse.

71
00:05:16,633 --> 00:05:20,833
And God forbid, you can die!

72
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:23,033
I can't bear it, Mookie.

73
00:05:24,467 --> 00:05:26,667
Dear, I can't bear it.

74
00:05:26,733 --> 00:05:28,800
I can't live alone.

75
00:05:28,867 --> 00:05:30,533
So, please.

76
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:32,767
I'm begging you.

77
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:36,567
Take your medicines, please.

78
00:05:36,667 --> 00:05:39,533
I don't want anything bad
to happen to you, dear.

79
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:40,800
Please.

80
00:05:46,167 --> 00:05:48,467
Please. I'm begging you.

81
00:05:48,533 --> 00:05:49,300
Please.

82
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:51,333
Okay, Mommy.

83
00:05:52,733 --> 00:05:54,867
Please hand me my medicines.

84
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:37,100
Thank you, dear.

85
00:06:37,167 --> 00:06:38,000
Thank you.

86
00:06:45,667 --> 00:06:46,867
Go get some rest.

87
00:07:27,467 --> 00:07:28,533
Mookie?

88
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:32,100
What's that?

89
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:35,800
Aren't you taking
your medicines?

90
00:07:36,667 --> 00:07:37,467
Why?
Give it to me.

91
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:47,900
I feel that I get worse
whenever I take them.

92
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:52,900
I haven't taken my
medicines for days now,

93
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:55,200
but look at me.

94
00:07:55,267 --> 00:07:56,933
I'm still okay.

95
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,700
I'm feeling well.

96
00:07:58,767 --> 00:08:00,400
Oh, dear.

97
00:08:00,467 --> 00:08:03,167
Do you think your mom

98
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:06,233
will give you medicines
you don't need?

99
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,533
I'm not sure, Flor.

100
00:08:11,433 --> 00:08:14,100
Mommy is insisting I'm sick.

101
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:19,000
Even though I feel otherwise.

102
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,367
And she's not a doctor.

103
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:25,200
What did you say?

104
00:08:26,867 --> 00:08:28,600
Your mom isn't a doctor?

105
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:31,733
That's it, Flor.

106
00:08:33,233 --> 00:08:35,033
That's where I'm confused.

107
00:08:36,967 --> 00:08:40,267
I don't know what's the truth.

108
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,633
I'm not sure if I'm sick or not.

109
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:47,300
And if I'm not sick...

110
00:08:50,133 --> 00:08:52,000
why is mommy doing this?

111
00:08:53,133 --> 00:08:54,700
What's the reason?

112
00:08:55,967 --> 00:08:56,933
Mookie...

113
00:08:58,333 --> 00:09:01,567
I can't answer your questions.

114
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:05,133
But if your mom isn't
a licensed doctor,

115
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:09,767
you must get checked by
a real one to know the truth.

116
00:09:18,967 --> 00:09:20,633
Just put it here, Obet.

117
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:22,500
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Careful. Put it here.

118
00:09:23,267 --> 00:09:24,267
There.

119
00:09:24,967 --> 00:09:25,567
Thank you.

120
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:28,533
Obet, bring this to finance.

121
00:09:28,633 --> 00:09:29,267
Okay, Ma'am.
Excuse me.

122
00:09:38,633 --> 00:09:39,767
Olive?

123
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:41,833
Why do you seem distracted?

124
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:47,767
Mookie doesn't want
to take her medicines.

125
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:49,567
She suspects she isn't sick

126
00:09:49,633 --> 00:09:52,000
because she saw her
old medical records.

127
00:09:52,733 --> 00:09:55,467
And she talked to Doctor...

128
00:10:01,167 --> 00:10:02,167
Wait a minute.

129
00:10:03,933 --> 00:10:08,233
Did you give Mookie
Doc Charles's number?

130
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:09,633
What?
No!

131
00:10:11,067 --> 00:10:12,500
I'd have to answer
to you if I did.

132
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,533
I wonder.

133
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:21,767
Olive, I think it's time
for you to tell Mookie the truth

134
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:23,467
if she's already suspecting.

135
00:10:24,067 --> 00:10:28,733
And please, stop giving her
medicines she doesn't need.

136
00:10:42,867 --> 00:10:46,367
I'm not asking for your opinion.

137
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,300
Some people reported to me

138
00:10:58,367 --> 00:11:01,800
a car driving around
Purok 2 back then.

139
00:11:01,867 --> 00:11:04,000
I ignored it because
it didn't have something to do

140
00:11:04,067 --> 00:11:05,933
with the landslide.

141
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,767
I never considered that it was
related to what happened to you.

142
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:14,367
But, Captain, did they describe
what the car looks like?

143
00:11:14,433 --> 00:11:15,067
Yes.

144
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:18,233
It was a gray car.

145
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:19,433
Wait, Sir.

146
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:24,733
When I was rescuing my family,
I saw a gray car.

147
00:11:26,967 --> 00:11:27,867
I remember it now.

148
00:11:28,433 --> 00:11:29,667
That's the same color

149
00:11:29,733 --> 00:11:32,200
of the car of the woman
who took Kayla.

150
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:41,700
Wait! I forgot!
I'm cooking something!

151
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:42,700
Oh, no!

152
00:11:42,767 --> 00:11:44,700
It might get burned.

153
00:11:44,767 --> 00:11:45,900
Oh, boy!

154
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:54,600
Mookie!

155
00:11:55,433 --> 00:11:56,500
Is your mom there?

156
00:11:57,767 --> 00:11:58,500
She's not here.

157
00:12:01,633 --> 00:12:02,467
How are you?

158
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:05,600
I'm still confused.

159
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,233
You know, I have a feeling

160
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:10,167
that mommy's keeping
something from me.

161
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:14,567
Zayn, can you help me?

162
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:18,267
I want to go to the
hospital to get checked.

163
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:19,100
Of course.

164
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:20,667
I'll go with you.

165
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:22,167
Really?

166
00:12:22,767 --> 00:12:23,333
Yes.
Thank you.

167
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,533
Should we go now?

168
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,733
Yes.

169
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,833
My mom might come
home anytime.

170
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:32,033
Okay.

171
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:35,600
Zayn that's...
Keep this.

172
00:12:36,533 --> 00:12:37,367
Call me, okay?
- Call me.
- Okay.

173
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:38,567
Call me.
Okay.

174
00:12:51,567 --> 00:12:52,333
Flor!

175
00:12:54,433 --> 00:12:55,067
Flor!

176
00:12:56,767 --> 00:12:58,300
Flor, why is the gate open?

177
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:02,533
Mookie.

178
00:13:03,533 --> 00:13:05,667
- What are you doing outside?
- Mommy.

179
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:06,667
Is everything okay?

180
00:13:06,733 --> 00:13:08,167
Yes, Mommy.

181
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:10,667
I'm just eating and
catching some fresh air.

182
00:13:13,067 --> 00:13:14,000
Flor!

183
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,833
What are you looking at?

184
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,867
What are you looking at?

185
00:13:29,867 --> 00:13:30,733
Nothing.

186
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:42,033
Let's go, Mookie.

187
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:43,067
We have something
to talk about.

188
00:13:43,133 --> 00:13:44,233
Get up.

189
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:45,267
Flor!

190
00:13:48,633 --> 00:13:50,133
Flor, close the gate!

191
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:51,800
Yes, Ma'am.

192
00:14:04,467 --> 00:14:06,233
When you were a kid...

193
00:14:09,033 --> 00:14:11,267
you loved me unconditionally.

194
00:14:16,267 --> 00:14:18,033
But I'm disheartened now.

195
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:24,433
Because you're doubting
everything I do for you.

196
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,467
And even my love.

197
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:34,200
Before you came into my life...

198
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:37,600
I was so depressed.

199
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:44,033
Because I lost everything.

200
00:14:47,667 --> 00:14:50,567
I thought I would die
of loneliness.

201
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:54,433
No!

202
00:14:58,633 --> 00:15:02,200
I was ready to give up
on my life, and then...

203
00:15:12,267 --> 00:15:17,267
I fell in love the
first time I saw you.

204
00:15:18,433 --> 00:15:20,700
You made me live again.

205
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:26,433
That car was in a hurry.

206
00:15:27,033 --> 00:15:27,967
It seemed like it was
escaping from something.

207
00:15:28,033 --> 00:15:29,333
It kept on honking.

208
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:31,700
It even hit my trike
when she overtook me.

209
00:15:31,767 --> 00:15:33,700
Do you remember
where it stopped?

210
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:34,667
Yes.

211
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:37,067
10 minutes after
she overtook me,

212
00:15:37,133 --> 00:15:39,767
I passed by her car
in front of a big house.

213
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:56,333
Wait.

214
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:59,267
Is it near
Barangay Pinagkaisahan?

215
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:00,167
No.

216
00:16:00,933 --> 00:16:02,567
I think it's almost
outside of Tanay.

217
00:16:03,433 --> 00:16:04,933
It's on the way to Manila.

218
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,800
So when I brought you
home that night,

219
00:16:16,267 --> 00:16:18,367
I made a promise to myself.

220
00:16:19,467 --> 00:16:20,867
From now on...

221
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:25,567
I'll be your mom.

222
00:16:25,633 --> 00:16:29,400
And I promise you that
I will take care of you.

223
00:16:29,467 --> 00:16:35,533
And I'll make sure that
we will never get separated.

224
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,400
I love you so much, Mookie.

225
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,467
You are my life.

226
00:16:43,533 --> 00:16:46,300
And I'm not capable
of hurting you.

227
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:50,767
Don't you believe mommy?

228
00:16:51,667 --> 00:16:55,633
I believe you, Mommy.
Promise.

229
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:57,067
Promise. But...

230
00:16:57,133 --> 00:16:59,533
You won't doubt everything
I do for you

231
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:01,767
if you love me, Mookie.

232
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:05,733
I don't want anything
but for you to get better.

233
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:18,900
Please.

234
00:17:20,067 --> 00:17:20,833
Please.

235
00:17:40,267 --> 00:17:41,667
That's my good girl.

236
00:17:54,733 --> 00:17:56,233
I'll change my clothes first.

237
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:44,167
Here.

238
00:18:44,733 --> 00:18:46,367
This is where I saw the
car of the woman

239
00:18:46,433 --> 00:18:48,033
who took your child.

240
00:18:48,100 --> 00:18:49,400
This is where I passed her by.

241
00:18:59,433 --> 00:19:00,867
Don't you get it, Jade?

242
00:19:01,467 --> 00:19:03,433
I don't want to have
anything to do with you,

243
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:04,867
so stop calling me!

244
00:19:04,933 --> 00:19:06,633
So grumpy!

245
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:10,833
Good morning, my sister, Olive!

246
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:12,833
I'm already in Manila.

247
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:14,800
The hell I care.

248
00:19:14,867 --> 00:19:17,233
Don't ever show up to me.

249
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:18,933
Sorry, but I have to.

250
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,233
I want to get my share
in our ancestral house.

251
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:24,100
I need money.

252
00:19:25,233 --> 00:19:26,000
Well...

253
00:19:26,933 --> 00:19:29,167
I have no plan of
selling the house.

254
00:19:29,967 --> 00:19:33,500
It's as if you have a choice
once I get the land title.

255
00:19:33,567 --> 00:19:35,000
Remember, Olive.

256
00:19:35,067 --> 00:19:37,600
We both have the right
to sell it.

257
00:19:37,667 --> 00:19:40,133
Don't ever try me, Jade!

258
00:19:40,867 --> 00:19:43,333
Bye!

259
00:19:46,467 --> 00:19:48,100
Darn that Jade!

260
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:50,900
You're adding to my problems!

261
00:20:00,067 --> 00:20:01,967
Looks like no one lives here.

262
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:03,200
It seems to be abandoned.

263
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:07,733
But I'm sure they
have a caretaker.

264
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:10,933
Thanks for your help, Bukoy.

265
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:14,400
Maybe Emma and I will just
wait for whoever will come.

266
00:20:15,367 --> 00:20:16,033
Okay.

267
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:17,467
Good luck.

268
00:20:17,533 --> 00:20:19,000
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

269
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:27,100
Hello, Mister Ando.

270
00:20:27,167 --> 00:20:28,867
I'm on my way there.

271
00:20:28,933 --> 00:20:31,000
I'll probably be
there in one hour.

272
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:33,033
I checked the app,
and there's no traffic.

273
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,700
But Jade might arrive
before I do.

274
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,433
She also has a key
to daddy's vault,

275
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:39,167
where the land title is kept.

276
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:41,700
Mookie, dear.

277
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:45,000
Mommy has to go.

278
00:20:45,067 --> 00:20:47,133
I need to fix something.

279
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,800
I'll come home late. Okay?

280
00:20:48,867 --> 00:20:50,067
Don't wait for me.

281
00:20:50,133 --> 00:20:51,467
- Flor?
- Yes, Ma'am.

282
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:57,867
Keep an eye on Mookie.

283
00:20:58,667 --> 00:21:00,667
Make sure she won't go out
of the house.

284
00:21:00,733 --> 00:21:01,433
Yes, Ma'am.

285
00:21:20,567 --> 00:21:21,267
Zayn?

286
00:21:22,067 --> 00:21:23,800
Zayn, can you come with me?

287
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:25,100
Okay, Mookie.

288
00:21:25,167 --> 00:21:26,200
I'm just near your house.

289
00:21:26,267 --> 00:21:27,200
Okay.

290
00:21:27,667 --> 00:21:28,433
Flor!

291
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,533
Flor! Wait.

292
00:21:32,367 --> 00:21:33,833
Zayn's coming.

293
00:21:34,167 --> 00:21:34,767
What?

294
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:38,167
Mookie, I can't let you go out.

295
00:21:38,233 --> 00:21:40,767
Your mom wants you to stay here.

296
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:42,000
Please, Flor.

297
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:43,400
This is my chance.

298
00:21:43,467 --> 00:21:46,900
You told me to see
a real doctor.

299
00:21:46,967 --> 00:21:47,933
Come on, Mookie.

300
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:50,533
I'll be in trouble.

301
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,233
Please, Flor.

302
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:56,033
I want to know
my real condition.

303
00:21:56,100 --> 00:22:00,833
Mookie, I might lose my job.

304
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:02,100
Please, Flor.

305
00:22:02,167 --> 00:22:06,567
You know I want
to help you, but...

306
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,533
Okay, okay.

307
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:13,633
I'll let you go out.

308
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:15,233
But don't take long, okay?

309
00:22:16,033 --> 00:22:17,267
Come back right away.

310
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:18,300
Yes, Flor.

311
00:22:18,367 --> 00:22:19,067
Come back quick.
Thank you.

312
00:22:19,933 --> 00:22:20,700
Okay.
He's here.

313
00:22:21,233 --> 00:22:21,900
Zayn's here.

314
00:22:21,967 --> 00:22:23,267
Careful.

315
00:22:23,333 --> 00:22:24,900
Come home quick, okay?

316
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:26,700
Mookie!

317
00:22:27,933 --> 00:22:28,700
Are you okay?

318
00:22:29,100 --> 00:22:29,700
Let's go?

319
00:22:30,500 --> 00:22:31,667
Let me hold this.

320
00:22:32,633 --> 00:22:33,900
I'll hold it.

321
00:22:33,967 --> 00:22:34,633
Okay.

322
00:22:35,167 --> 00:22:35,833
I'll assist Mookie.

323
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:36,933
Slowly.

324
00:22:37,733 --> 00:22:38,500
Careful.

325
00:22:38,567 --> 00:22:40,100
I'll put this at the back.

326
00:23:02,033 --> 00:23:03,400
Look at the two cars.

327
00:23:04,067 --> 00:23:06,233
Maybe one of them is
the one we're looking for.

328
00:23:07,933 --> 00:23:09,633
I'll check on it.

329
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:13,833
Who's that?

330
00:23:16,067 --> 00:23:16,767
Dan.
Dan!

331
00:23:22,733 --> 00:23:23,933
Slowly, Mookie.

332
00:23:25,067 --> 00:23:25,700
Are you okay?

333
00:23:27,133 --> 00:23:28,167
Let's go over there.

334
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:33,467
Careful.

335
00:23:37,567 --> 00:23:38,267
Okay.

336
00:23:49,967 --> 00:23:50,867
What do you need?

337
00:23:51,667 --> 00:23:52,733
Go, Mookie.

338
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:53,467
Tell her.

339
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:58,400
Hello, I want to
get myself checked.

340
00:23:58,500 --> 00:24:01,767
I want to know if
I'm really sick.

341
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:03,933
Are you with your parent?

342
00:24:08,833 --> 00:24:10,233
No.

343
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:11,467
How old are you?

344
00:24:13,533 --> 00:24:14,833
17.

345
00:24:16,067 --> 00:24:19,633
I'm her guardian,
so I'm responsible for her.

346
00:24:25,833 --> 00:24:27,867
Wait, I'll get you a form.

347
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:05,500
Hey!

348
00:25:09,167 --> 00:25:10,100
Darn you!

349
00:25:10,167 --> 00:25:11,467
Are you going to kill me?

350
00:25:13,367 --> 00:25:14,367
- Sir.
- Hey!

351
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:17,233
What are you doing there?

352
00:25:17,300 --> 00:25:19,500
We only want to
ask you something.

353
00:25:19,567 --> 00:25:20,600
Who are you?

354
00:25:24,633 --> 00:25:25,700
- We want...
- What do you need?

355
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:29,200
We only want to know
who owns this house.

356
00:25:29,933 --> 00:25:30,767
That's all we need.

357
00:25:30,833 --> 00:25:31,967
He's long been dead.

358
00:25:33,167 --> 00:25:35,467
Who owns it now, Sir?

359
00:25:35,567 --> 00:25:37,833
Is she also the
owner in 2007?

360
00:25:37,900 --> 00:25:39,433
Where are they now?

361
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:41,400
This property
is not for sale.

362
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,433
And you're just
wasting your time

363
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:46,133
if you plan to rob this house.

364
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:47,533
There's nothing inside.

365
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:49,500
We're not thieves.

366
00:25:49,567 --> 00:25:51,933
Sir, we have no plans
to buy the property.

367
00:25:52,900 --> 00:25:54,700
We're also not thieves.

368
00:25:54,767 --> 00:25:56,167
So what are you doing here?

369
00:25:57,167 --> 00:25:59,300
The nerve of you to blame me.

370
00:25:59,367 --> 00:26:01,667
Aren't you the stupid
one who's not looking?

371
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:04,633
So arrogant.

372
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:12,033
Leave, or I'll call the cops.

373
00:26:13,067 --> 00:26:13,700
No need.

374
00:26:13,767 --> 00:26:15,067
We're leaving.

375
00:26:22,533 --> 00:26:25,300
I know how she longs
to see her child.

376
00:26:25,367 --> 00:26:27,967
Emma feels twice the pain.

377
00:26:28,033 --> 00:26:29,800
I gave my twins away.

378
00:26:29,867 --> 00:26:33,533
But Baby Kayla was
taken away from her.

379
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:35,467
You want to be tested
to determine

380
00:26:35,533 --> 00:26:38,733
if you really have an autoimmune
disease and leukemia?

381
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:41,500
I also want to know what
medications

382
00:26:41,567 --> 00:26:43,333
are being given to me.

383
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:46,000
Mookie?

384
00:26:46,567 --> 00:26:47,733
Mommy?
